cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.HC, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on teaching robots to dance and uses wheeled robots to replicate the movements of human dancers. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses motion control problems and communication objectives in the context of finite dimensional linear control systems. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper explores how mobile agents engaged in a shared activity such as dance can use motion as a medium for transmitting certain types of messages. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper evaluates dance performances by human dancers using judges and proposes complexity metrics. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper poses a general class of dual objective motion control problems and discusses solutions of varying degrees of explicitness.
